volume.name: Crossed: Wish You Were Here Interlude

deck: A collection of pages to color, activities, and stories featuring some of everyone's favorite Looney Tunes characters.
description:
Coloring Page

Taz the Tazmanian Devil is inked and ready to be colored

Shake Well Before Ewes

Ralph Wolf and Wile E. Coyote go to work. Ralph prevents Wile's repeated attempts to steal sheep.

Bugs Bunny & Yosemite Sam Con-Fuse-Ion Take One

One page story where Yosemite Sam attempts to blow up Bugs Bunny in his hole. The outcome is predictable. Hint: Sam is left holding the dynamite when it explodes.

Fowled Out

Wile E. Coyote attempts to catch the Road Runner. The sports-themed traps include exploding hockey pucks, giant cricket bats (and even more giant crickets), dynamite filled bowling balls, and more.

Bugs Bunny & Yosemite Sam Con-Fuse-Ion Take Two

Once again Sam is left holding the dynamite.

Tweety Temps!

The fourth wall is partially broken when Sylvester Pussycat is filming an episode of the standard cartoon featuring Tweety Bird. In this tale Tweety is played by a number of other Looney Tunes characters. Most notable is the arms race between Sylvester and Daffy Duck.

Bugs Bunny & Yosemite Sam Con-Fuse-Ion Take Three

Bugs once again outsmarts Sam in the latter's attempt to dynamite the former in his hole.

Coloring Page

Petunia Pig and Porky Pig are inked and ready for coloring.

Looney Tunes Silhouettes

An activity page encouraging readers to "Find Daffy Duck's identical silhouette".

deck: A collection of pages to color, activities, and stories featuring some of everyone's favorite Looney Tunes characters.
description:
A page to color

An inked page ready to color featuring Bugs Bunny and Marvin The Martian.

Oh, Baby

Daffy Duck is given a job as a daycare worker. As he starts reading the children their numbers begin to swell. They're coming from his Acme sack and their use of the items in the sack is wreaking havoc on the building. Eventually Daffy is himself turned into a toddler.

Birdie-Go Vertigo!

Sylvester Pussycat develops vertigo when he falls off a ladder while attempting to catch Tweety Bird. Eventually this causes him to fall off the top of a building under construction while chasing Tweety.

Life In The Crash Lane

Wile E. Coyote is on the wrong end of numerous traps he uses in an attempt to capture Road Runner.

Carrot Conquest

Marvin The Martian comes to Earth to collect carrotonium. Unfortunately for him he attempts to take it from Bugs Bunny. Even with the help of K-9 Bugs continues to get the better of Marvin, eventually sending him up to the land of the giants in the clouds.

Hare Sighted

Bugs Bunny lures Yosemite Sam into a house of mirrors and convinces him that he's going insane. Sam is eventually carted off to the loony bin.

Looney Tunes Silhouettes

An activity page where the reader is encouraged to "Find the Tasmanian Devil's identical silhouette!" featuring Taz.
Lord Superman vs. Wonder Woman—a husband and wife clash years in the making. Meanwhile, a tempting offer is made to Mr. Miracle…
name: Justice Lords Beyond: The Return of Wonder Woman, Part 6 of 8: World War

description:
Without peering into a mirror, it's not often you find yourself looking at your double, but that's what the quivering Jelly Jakes of the Convict Commandos was doing. He didn't like it one bit, especially as the man facing him was backed with four T34 tanks and about 20 heavily-armed Soviet infantrymen.

To make matters just that little bit worse, the man whose face he was staring at was justly known as..... "The Devil's Shadow"
name: Convict Commandos - The Devil's Shadow

description:
"Trouble squad" they were called. When a task was "impossible" - a mission so dangerous that it looked like certain death - the army sent for Trouble Squad. And the man who led this bunch of hard cases was the toughest of them all - Sergeant "Rocky" Flint. He'd trained them, forged them into fighting machines who could force-march twenty miles in three hours, go three days in the desert on a cup of water, and then take a force of Germans outnumbering them by three to one and smash them to a pulp!

They didn't call Flint "The Iron Sergeant" for nothing!!

The Iron Sergent, originally Commando No 116 (May 1964), re-issued as No 639 (April 1972)
name: The Iron Sergeant

description:
Private Dan Vaughn was a bit of a layabout. He didn't particularly like soldiering and his mate, Private Ian Hicks, was a constantly nagging at him to make an effort.

On Crete in 1941, they had a simple task, to transport some ammo in a Bedford truck. But - after an encounter with a low-flying enemy glider - Dan found himself in the middle of a battle, on involving Cretan partisans, crack German paratroopers and the SS.

Lying about was no longer an option if Dan wanted to stay alive!
name: Crisis On Crete

description:
As boys they had hated the sight of each other, and now they where rivals to command the same RAF fighter squadron. One was a regular officer who knew all the right people...the other was an "upstart", but he had been blooded against an enemy who gave no quarter.

Either one might end up in charge, but what neither could forget was that in war all the peace-time rules go out the window...survival becomes the name of the game.

Baptism Of Fire, originally Commando No 2317 (October 1989), re-issued as No 3883 (February 2006)

Its worth noting that while this is a re-issue of the original No 2317 and No 3883 the artwork on 4718 has been altered.
name: Baptism Of Fire

deck: The story follows up the events in Dan Abanett's novel Know No Fear. Calth is in ruin, but Word Bearer failed to bring down Macragge and destory the Ultramarine. Kor Phaeron was mortally wounded by Roboute Guilliman, Primarch of the XIII legion and was fleeting via Infidus Imperator. Guilliman sent Marius Gage, his second in command to hunt him down and avenge those who fallen in the surprise attack.
description:
After the surprise attack on Calth, World Bearer failed to destroy the Veridian System, and their commander, Kor Phaeron the black cardinal is mortally wounded by Roboute Guiliman and managed to use sorcery to escape to his flagship Infidus Imperator. Roboute Guiliman ask Marius Gage, Chapter Master of the First Chapter of the XIII Legion to hunt down the traitors responsible for the death of countless civilians and XIII Legion battle brothers.

Kor Phaeron was brought back to life with the help of his crew and the genetic argumentation. He planed on killing the Macragge's Honor's crew by summoning his daemonic allies, and then lead them into the warp where his dark gods masters. However, the Ultramarine eventually crash the Infidus Imperator. Kor Phaeron and his crew managed to fleed to the Eye of Terror via warp-sorcery and leaving Macragge's Honor wander aimlessly in the warp
name: Macragge's Honor
Night of the Mockers/By The Dawn's Early Light

description:
Ten years ago, we dug too deep. We unleashed something ancient that couldn't be controlled. Something that couldn't be stopped, twisting everything it touched into more of itself. The Spread.

Humanity was nearly destroyed before we found a way to slow the Spread to a crawl. Now, deep inside the quarantined zone, one man has found the key to stopping it forever: a baby girl. And if he can save her, he might save the world.
